<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tehran Mayor Freed After Top-Level Intervention </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Detained Tehran Mayor
Gholamhussein Karbaschi was set free on bail on Wednesday after
the Supreme Leader Ayatollah Ali Khamenei endorsed the release.
</P>
<P>
The official news agency IRNA reported the release in a short
dispatch, without giving any details on the controversial case
that has tipped moderates against hardliners and triggered off
massive protests.
</P>
<P>
Informed sources here said the release came only after the
supreme leader held discussions with former President Hashemi
Rafsanjani, who now heads the influential State Expediency
Council, and received a written appeal from sitting President
Mohammad Khatami.
</P>
<P>
Karbaschi, 44, is a close ally of Iran's moderate President
Mohammad Khatami. He was detained on April 4 by the hardliner-led
judiciary on charges of embezzlement, misappropriation of funds
and mismanagement.
</P>
<P>
Local press reports said Karbaschi was hated by hardliners
because he had channeled municipal funds to help Khatami's
presidential campaign that resulted in a humiliating defeat for
his hardline rival.
</P>
<P>
Political analysts here believe that intervention by Iran's top
notch is aimed at containing the dispute between different
political factions. Demonstrators demanding Karbaschi's release
clashed with police in the capital on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Moderates have rejected the charges against the mayor and said
the detention was politically motivated in an attempt to weaken
the government of Khatami. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
