<HEADLINE> Tanzania's First Stock Exchange Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, April 15 (Xinhua) -- The Dar es Salaam Stock
Exchange (DSE), the first in Tanzania, opened here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A total of 1,350 shares of the Tanzania Oxygen Limited (TOL), the
sole company that has been listed at the stock exchange, were
traded by five licensed dealers from 10:00 a.m. to 10:30 a.m..
</P>
<P>
One share of the TOL, a leading manufacturer and distributor
of industrial and medical gases in the east African country,
opened at 500 Shillings and closed at 510 Shillings.
</P>
<P>
The Director of DSE, Dr Hamisi Kibola, told Xinhua that the
stock exchange opens once a week since only one company has been
listed so far. But he said more profitable companies have lined
up for issuing stocks to the public.
</P>
<P>
The 7.5 million shares floated by TOL worth 37.5 billion
Shillings were bought by 10,000 shareholders from the end of last
year to March this year. President Mkapa has bought 100 shares
worth 50,000 Shillings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
