<HEADLINE> 18 Killed in S. African Road Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Eighteen people, including 15
school children, were killed and at least 70 others were injured Wednesday
afternoon in a five-vehicle smash in Newcastle, Kwazulu-Natal
Province, South African Press Association (SAPA) reported.
</P>
<P>
SAPA quoted police spokesman Godfrey Nyembe as saying that the
accident happen at 2.50 p.m. (1250 GMT) in an industrial area outside
Newcastle, a city about 300 kilometers southeast of Johannesburg.
</P>
<P>
Nyembe said the police were investigating the cause of the crash,
but said a horse and trailer, a private school bus, a car, a minibus
and a light truck were involved in the accident.
</P>
<P>
He said most of the injured were in a serious condition and a
number had suffered severed limbs.
</P>
<P>
The injured were being treated at two hospitals in Newcastle.
</P>
<P>
He said rescue workers were still removing bodies from the wreckage
at 6 p.m. (1600 GMT). 
</P>
</TEXT>
