resolve to stay in Kuwait until we are completely clear that
Saddam Hussein will abide by the agreement with the U.N.," said a
British official.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the Tornado planes stationed in Kuwait, Britain
has six attack aircraft in Saudi Arabia and another six in Turkey.
