<HEADLINE> Cyprus Plans to Cancel Interest Rates Ceiling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus has planned to cancel the
ceiling for interest rates in view of its accession talks with the
European Union (EU), according to Finance Minister Christodoulos
Christodoulou on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The plan is aimed at liberalizing the interest rates,
Christodoulou told reporters after a meeting with Afxentis
Afxentiou, governor of Cyprus' central bank.
</P>
<P>
The government will submit a bill in this regard to the House
of Representatives no later than June for approval, he added.
</P>
<P>
The ceiling has been imposed on the interest rates under the present
Cypriot legislation.
</P>
<P>
The ceiling must be abolished in a bid to promote Cyprus'
accession talks with the EU and modernize its financial system,
Christodoulou said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the move is in line with the liberalization of
the global economy and the international financial system.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus, along with five Central and Eastern European states,
began entry talks with the EU last month. 
</P>
