Zyuganov as saying that the Duma will not approve Kiriyenko as
prime minister at the second ballot on April 17. Communist
deputies in the Duma will vote against Kiriyenko, he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Gennady Seleznyov, the Chairman of the State Duma,
has changed his Tuesday's predication that Kiriyenko was very
likely to be approved by the Duma in the second try.
</P>
<P>
Seleznyov on Wednesday said he was not sure the persident's
nominee would be able to win 226 votes of lawmakers necessary to
secure him the post. 
