<HEADLINE> S. African Horror Smash Kills 18 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Eighteen people, including
15 school children, were killed Wednesday afternoon in a
five-vehicle smash in Newcastle, Kwazulu-Natal province, South
African Press Association (SAPA) reported.
</P>
<P>
SAPA said 44 people were wounded during the accident,
correcting the figure of 70 injured as it reported earlier on the
event.
</P>
<P>
SAPA quoted police spokesman Godfrey Nyembe as saying that the
accident happened at 14:50 p.m. (12:50 GMT) in an industrial area
outside Newcastle, a city about 300 kilometers southeast of
Johannesburg.
</P>
<P>
Nyembe said the police were investigating the cause of the
crash, but said a horse and trailer, a private school bus, a car,
a mini-bus and a light truck were involved in the accident.
</P>
<P>
Kwazulu-Natal traffic spokesman Vijen Murugan said four of the
vehicles, including the school bus and the horse and trailer,
plunged down a 50-meter embankment.
</P>
<P>
Murugan said the school bus was transporting primary school
children from three nearby schools.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the accident was unknown.
</P>
<P>
Nyembe said most of the injured were in a serious condition
and some had suffered severed limbs.
</P>
<P>
The injured were being treated at two hospitals in Newcastle.
</P>
<P>
Rescue workers were still removing bodies from the wreckage at
18:00 p.m. (16:00 GMT), Nyembe said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
