<HEADLINE> About 40 People Injured in Highway Traffic Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 15 (Xinhua) -- About 40 people were injured
in a highway accident that involved some 30 vehicles in Missouri
Wednesday morning, the Associated Press reported.
</P>
<P>
The vehicles were piled up on rain-slick pavement on a section
of eastbound Interstate 70 which was shut down by the pile-up.
</P>
<P>
A heavy rain had fallen on the area during the night, but the
cause of the wreck was not immediately determined.
</P>
<P>
Four of the injured were in serious condition but was stable at
a nearby hospital. Their injuries ranged from concussions and
other head injuries to abdominal injuries and broken bones.
</P>
<P>
The other injured were also taken by bus to hospitals and many
were treated and released. 
</P>
