<HEADLINE> Austrian FM in Cyprus for Talks on EU Course </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Austrian Vice Chancellor and
Federal Minister of Foreign Affairs, Wolfgang Schussel, arrived
here Wednesday for talks with the Cypriot government on European
Union (EU) course.
</P>
<P>
Schussel's two-day visit comes only three months before
Austria takes over the rotating presidency of the EU, currently
held by Britain.
</P>
<P>
Speaking upon his arrival, Schussel said his talks here
will deal with "the issues, the problems, the possibilities and
the perspectives" regarding the EU and Cyprus' accession.
</P>
<P>
"I think it is a good time to visit Cyprus to prepare
ourselves to meet the relevant personalities and have full
access to relevant information and to the people of Cyprus,"
the Austrian Vice Chancellor told reporters.
</P>
<P>
He said his country was looking forward to taking the EU
presidency, which he described as a "big challenge".
</P>
<P>
"I am looking forward to talking tomorrow with all the
important politicians and personalities of Cyprus about the
relevant issues," he added.
</P>
<P>
Welcoming his guest, Cyprus Foreign Minister Ioannis Kasoulides
said the visit demonstrated Austria's great interest in Cyprus,
adding that this visit is particularly important since Austria
will be assuming the presidency of the EU for the second part
of 1998.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Schussel is expected to have meetings
with President Glafcos Clerides and other government officials, as
well as U.N. Resident Representative in Cyprus Gustave Feissel.
</P>
<P>
He will also visit members of the Austrian contingent
serving with the U.N. Peace-Keeping Force in the eastern part
of the island. 
</P>
</TEXT>
