<HEADLINE> Egyptian FM Leaves for Bahrain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr
Moussa left here Wednesday evening for Manama on a two-day visit
to Bahrain.
</P>
<P>
Moussa is to convey a message from President Hosni Mubarak to
Bahraini Emir Sheikh Isa Bin Sulman Al-Khalifa, the Middle East
News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
In pre-departure statements, Moussa said that he is to hold
talks with a number of senior Bahraini officials on bilateral
relations, the Arab situation and the recent developments in the
Middle East and the Gulf region.
</P>
<P>
Moussa noted that he will also hold talks with his Bahraini
counterpart Sheikh Mohammed Bin Mubarak Al-Khalifa.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian foreign minister is expected to give a lecture on
Thursday in Manama on the Arab vision on the Mideast peace process
before returning home on Friday to attend the Egyptian-British
talks.
</P>
<P>
British Prime Minister Tony Blair will start a two-day visit to
Egypt on Friday to promote the European role in the stalled peace
process.
</P>
<P>
Blair's first Mideast tour will also take him to Saudi Arabia,
Jordan, Israel and the Palestinian National Authority. 
</P>
