<HEADLINE> Heavy Rains Kill Two in N. Rwanda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Heavy rains have killed two
people in Nyakinama Commune, in Rwanda's northern Ruhengeri
Prefecture, the Rwanda News Agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Due to the recent heavy rains that have been falling in the
Virunga mountains Range, two rivers of the area swelled over
their banks, causing immense destruction to houses and farmlands,
the report said.
</P>
<P>
The catastrophe has also left 82 families homeless. The last
time such heavy rains fell on the region was in May 1988, when
320 families were also displaced. 
</P>
