<HEADLINE> Cyprus to Invest More in Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus will invest 200-250
million pounds (about 400-500 million U.S. dollars) in tourism,
the Financial Mirror newspaper reported on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted Cypriot Minister of Commerce, Industry and
Tourism Nicos Rolandis as saying that Cyprus has so far invested
1.5 billion pounds (3 billion dollars) in the sector.
</P>
<P>
The tourism industry is Cyprus' most dynamic economic
sector. It accounts for 20 percent of the 4.3-billion-pound
(8.6-billion-dollar) gross domestic product of the Mediterranean
island.
</P>
<P>
The minister expected more than 2 million tourists to visit his
country this year, an increase of 5 to 10 percent from 1997.
</P>
