<HEADLINE> Four Killed by Tornadoes in U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 16 (Xinhua) -- At least four people were
killed and 22 others injured by a tornado that struck northeastern
Arkansas and western Tennessee early Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Two were killed in Manila, Arkansas, around 3 a.m. local time
and two others an hour later in southeast Dyer County, Tennessee,
an Associated Press report said.
</P>
<P>
Buildings also were damaged at Jonesboro and Blytheville in
northeastern Arkansas. Two hundred structures, including some
mobile homes, in the Manila area were damaged, the report said.
</P>
<P>
In Manila, a factory that rebuilds brake parts and another that
makes hydraulic lifts were among the buildings damaged. 
</P>
