<HEADLINE> Officials Punished for Dereliction of Duty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, April 16 (Xinhua) -- The Communist Party Committee of
Luliang Prefecture in north China's Shanxi Province announced
today that 24 officials have been punished in line with Party and
administrative discipline procedures for dereliction of duty
involving their failure to inspect counterfeit spirits.
</P>
<P>
In January this year, farmers in a number of locations
throughout Shanxi distilled and sold counterfeit low quality
spirits which killed 26 and poisoned hundreds of people. Six
perpetrators were sentenced to death on March 9 with the approval
of the Supreme People's Court, with various others subject to
differing degrees of punishment.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin expressed great concern for the incident,
and local governments in Shanxi have since investigated cases
involving alleged dereliction of duty.
</P>
<P>
The 24 people punished included one prefectural official and
five county-level officials, including Li Liulan, secretary of the
Communist Party Committee of Wenshui County, Wenshui Magistrate
Song Weimin and Deputy Magistrate Cheng Haihan, and Vice-Mayor Li
Guangmao of Fenyang City.
</P>
<P>
A number of officials in charge of quality inspection of liquor
were also penalized for neglecting their duties.
</P>
<P>
Various officials were subject to Party warnings or major
administrative demerits on their records, with other either
expelled from the Party or removed from their official posts.
</P>
</TEXT>
