<DOCNO> XIE19980416.0080 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Enterprises Favor Patent Applications </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 16 (Xinhua) -- China's industrial enterprises
have exhibited an increasing preference for intellectual property
rights.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics released today by the State
Intellectual Property Office (SIPO), the number of patent
applications from Chinese industrial enterprises increased by 25
percent last year from 1996.
</P>
<P>
Chinese industrial enterprises made a record 25,469 Patent
applications in 1997, as against 7,020 in 1991, according to
statistics.
</P>
<P>
The Haier Group, China's major manufacturer of household
electrical appliances located in Qingdao, Shandong Province, led
the nation's business sector in patent applications for
technological inventions and designs.
</P>
<P>
The top 10 enterprises in patent applications included the
China Petrochemical Corporation and the Shanghai-based Baoshan
Steel Group.
</P>
<P>
The nation's scientific research institutes have submitted
2,000 applications annually in the past seven years, with
the number of applications from universities and colleges
declining on an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
Statistics also revealed that economically developed coastal
areas and provinces in south China led the nation in terms of
applications. For example, Guangdong Province, an economic
powerhouse neighboring Hong Kong, accounted for nearly 15 percent
of the total patent applications in 1997.
</P>
<P>
China has standardized competition between domestic businesses
by strengthening the protection of intellectual property
rights, according to a SIPO official.
</P>
<P>
Patents granted to multinational corporations have not only
provided China with information about the development of the
high-tech industry but also sparked an increase in foreign
investments, the official said.
</P>
<P>
China adopted its first Patent Law in 1993 and in the following
year signed the Patent Cooperation Treaty (PCT) formulated by the
World Intellectual Property Organization. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
