United States was established here today by the China Textile
International Exchange Center, China National Research and Design
Center, and the US-base Da Loo Fashion Group.
</P>
<P>
The Sino-US Apparel Association, which have offices in Beijing
and Chicago, is expected to help increase sales of Chinese-made
garments on the U.S. market.
</P>
<P>
The association, which also will help China import new fashion
technology and designs from the US, will extend great effort to
add impetus to the reform and improvement of China's textile and
garment industries.
</P>
<P>
It will also draft plans for technological and trade
cooperation between the two countries, provide timely
international information on textiles and apparels, help industry
sources in two countries participate in apparel fairs, organize
training programs and performances, and help promote name brand
garments in the respective markets.
</P>
<P>
China's textile and garment industries have witnessed rapid
development in recent years. However, a gap still remains in
China's efforts to equal world standards related to design and the
development of name brand garments and high-grade fabrics. 
