<HEADLINE> Internet Stocks Rising to Dizzying High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Investors continued to pile onto
the Internet bandwagon today, powering stocks to new highs as
Yahoo showed the sector can be profitable.
</P>
<P>
Yahoo Inc, the famous search engine maker on the Internet, has
been chased by buyers over the past few weeks and its stock price
has been pushed as high as 119 U.S. dollars at the opening today.
</P>
<P>
It retreated a bit as the broad market dipped at profit taking
after the Dow Jones industrial average set new highs over the past
two sessions on end.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, the American Stock Exchange of Internet stocks
was up 2.5 percent as the sector sprinted ahead of the broader
market.
</P>
<P>
Some analysts believed that as Compaq and other computer
hardware companies missed earnings estimates, a lot of
institutional money were turned into Internet stocks.
</P>
<P>
Yahoo's stock price was just a bit more than 20 U.S. dollars
last June and it jumped to 60 dollars by the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
Talk of a stock split at Yahoo also is fueling the share
price, said analysts, who cautioned that the dizzying rise makes
Internet stocks vulnerable to a sharp pullback.  
</P>
</TEXT>
