<HEADLINE> Illegal Immigration Threating Romania's Security: Police </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Illegal immigrates are threats
to Romania's national security, the Romanian newspaper, The Truth,
reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"Illegal immigration has greatly damaged the country," the
newspaper quoted a senior police officer as saying.
</P>
<P>
The government will take severe measures to stop the
phenomenon, the officer said.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that illegal immigrates from Asian and the CIS
countries always transit Romania to the Western European nations
and, in 1997 alone, they committed more than 2,200 crimes here.
</P>
<P>
The officer blamed this situation on Romania's diplomatic
representatives' offices overseas, because it was too easy for
these dubious foreigners, some of them noted criminal offenders,
to get Romanian visas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
