<HEADLINE> Beijing Hosts Russian Cultural Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 16 (Xinhua) -- The Russian Cultural Festival
opened here today, with the Russian State Folk Dance Company
giving an evening performance.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Culture Minister Sun Jiazheng addressed the opening
ceremony and noted that the festival is an important event in
the Sino-Russian cultural exchanges.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that the festival will serve as a new
starting point for bilateral cultural exchanges and build a
cultural bridge of friendship between the two nations.
</P>
<P>
Acting Russian Culture Minister Natalia Dementyeva said on the
occasion that the Russian and Chinese peoples share equal
enjoyment for the culture of their counterpart.
</P>
<P>
The festival is aimed at enhancing the Chinese people's
understanding of Russian culture and promoting the development
of bilateral cultural relations, Natalia Dementyeva said.
</P>
<P>
The Russian State Folk Dance Company has visited China for
three times, in addition to more than 60 countries, since its
founding 50 years ago.
</P>
<P>
The festival is part of the 1997-98 cultural cooperative
plan formulated by the two governments.
</P>
<P>
Russia has sent a 150-member delegation to attend the
festival. It consists of government officials, experts in the
field of literature and art, and artists from 11 art troupes.
</P>
