<HEADLINE> Nepali PM Meets Senior Chinese Trade Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Nepali new Prime Minister
Girija Prasad Koirala said Thursday that during his term of
office, he will try his best to strengthen Sino-Nepalese ties and
friendship.
</P>
<P>
While meeting here with Liu Shanzai, China's vice minister for
foreign trade and economic cooperation, Koirala said Nepal and
China enjoy very cordial relations, and for years China has
provided different kinds of economic support and cooperation to
Nepal.
</P>
<P>
Economic cooperation and joint ventures will help strengthen
relations between the two governments and peoples, Koirala said.
</P>
<P>
Liu, who is heading an 18-member Chinese economic and trade
delegation, said he felt strongly that business-to-business
relations is a new area for strengthening economic cooperation
between China and Nepal.
</P>
<P>
He said that in the past two days, Chinese entrepreneurs
explored the possibility with their Nepalese counterparts of
setting up a cement factory and a farm tool manufacturer in Nepal.
</P>
<P>
And the Chinese government has decided to grant 400,000 RMB
yuan (48,309 U.S. dollars) to Nepal's non-governmental cooperation
forum to encourage business communities of the two countries to
strengthen cooperation, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has also decided to grant 30 million RMB
yuan (3.62 million dollars) in assistance to Nepal to finalize
projects agreed upon, he said.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the Chinese government will grant some quantity of
live sheep to Nepal before the grand festival of Dashain, Liu
said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese delegation arrived in Nepal on Tuesday for the 8th
session of the Nepal-China Inter-governmental Economic and Trade
Committee, which was established in 1983. 
</P>
</TEXT>
