<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jinan Hit by Dust Storm </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Numerous residents of Jinan,
capital of east China's Shandong Province, remained at home this
morning to escape the effects of severe dust storm which blew
through the region.
</P>
<P>
Vehicles were blanketed with thick layers of yellow dust and
pedestrians were covered with the dust after only a few minutes.
</P>
<P>
A report released by the city environmental supervision center
indicates that the storm hit about 04:00 this morning, with more
than one milligram of dust recorded per cubic meter of air. They
noted that the level far exceed state class-one air standards of
0.12 milligrams.
</P>
<P>
"The yellow dust in northwestern and north China resulted from
a cyclone in Mongolia, with dry and cold wind currents blowing the
dust to cities in eastern China, including Jinan," according to an
expert with the provincial meteorological department.
</P>
<P>
Dust storms occasionally hit northwestern cities, but are rare
in eastern parts of the country, according to experts.
</P>
<P>
But the dust storm "had little impact on flight schedules at
the city airport, " according to reliable sources.
</P>
<P>
The city meteorological department predicts that the north
winds will gradual weaken on Friday, with conditions expected to
return to normal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
