<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan to Have 1.1 Million Tons of Surplus Sugar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan will have a surplus of
1.1 million tons of sugar for export this year as a result of a
bumper sugarcane crop, the official Associated Press of Pakistan
(APP) said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The country's 73 sugar mills had turned out 3.25 million tons
of sugar by the end of March this year, APP said.
</P>
<P>
Industry sources are expecting an additional output of 250,000
tons of sugar by the mills till next month, which will make the
total output at 3.5 million tons this year.
</P>
<P>
The amount, together with the holdover stock of 400,000 tons,
makes a total availability of 3.9 million tons in the country.
</P>
<P>
After deducting the total domestic demand of 2.8 million tons,
the country will have a surplus stock of 1.1 million tons this
year, it said.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan reported a bumper crop of 52 million tons of sugarcane
last year, as the higher support price encouraged local growers to
cultivate more sugarcane.  
</P>
</TEXT>
