<HEADLINE> Liu Qi Appointed New Vice-Mayor of Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Liu Qi, a senior metallurgical
engineer and holder of a master's degree, was appointed vice-mayor
of Beijing during today's second session of the Standing Committee
of the 11th Beijing Municipal People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
Liu, 55, previously served as the minister of metallurgical
industry and secretary of the ministry's Communist Party
Committee.
</P>
<P>
Beijing, the Chinese capital, has a mayor and eight
vice-mayors. Seven of them hold master's degrees and one tutors
doctoral candidates.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Mayor Jia Qinglin said that Liu "possesses a wide range
of knowledge, and both strong organizational competence and
decision-making ability."
</P>
<P>
Liu Qi graduated from the Metallurgical Department at the
Beijing Institute of Iron and Steel Engineering in 1964, and
worked for many years at the Wuhan Iron and Steel Company in Hubei
Province.
</P>
<P>
Liu replaced former Beijing Vice-mayor Jin Renqing who was
recently appointed to serve as director of the State Taxation
Administration.
</P>
<P>
Liu is also a member of the 15th Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China. 
</P>
