<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Philippines rider Arnel Querimit
won a three-man sprint in the first stage of the Tour of the
Philippines on Thursday at central city Cebu of Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Querimit, 22, out-sprinted teammate Warren Davadilla and Nor
Effandy Rosli of Malaysia in the 190.30-kilometer lap from Cebu to
Bogo and back, taking over the yellow jersey from Filipino rookie
Virgilio Durain, Wednesday's prologue winner.
</P>
<P>
Defending champion Wong Kam Po of Hong Kong of China finished
well back in the pack and was more than 15 minutes behind of the
overall leader.
</P>
<P>
Riders will raced in Friday's second stage from Cebu and back
via the Argao resort south of the city, a 133.90-kilometer grind.
</P>
<P>
Six Asian national teams competed against Filipino riders in
this 2,570-kilometer, 16-stage tour with a total prize of 300,000
U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
