<HEADLINE> Gullit Sacked Because Chairman Feels Jealous </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Ruud Gullit said English
Premiership club Chelsea sacked him because Stamford Bridge
chairman Ken Bates felt jealous and uneasy of his success.
</P>
<P>
Gullit compared himself to former vice-chairman Matthew
Harding, who died in a helicopter crash, after he got too much
attention from his achievement.
</P>
<P>
But he said he did not regret being sacked because he could not
work any longer in that kind of atmosphere.
</P>
<P>
Gullit, who was never told the reason of being sacked , was
kicked out of the club on an excuse that his transfer budget was
too much to be accepted.
</P>
<P>
Chelsea is 1-0 down in the first leg of the European Cup
Winners' Cup clash with Vicenza and is bidding to turn around the
table in the return leg at home. 
</P>
