<HEADLINE> China Inks Railway Exchange Agreement with Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 16 (Xinhua) -- China and Japan signed an
agreement this afternoon calling for expanded cooperation between
their respective railway industries.
</P>
<P>
The goal of the agreement centers on promoting bilateral
exchanges and cooperation related to railway technology and
personnel training.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Railway Minister Fu Zhihuan and Nagamitsu Yoichi,
chairman of the Japan-China Railways Council (JCRC), signed the
agreement.
</P>
<P>
Wang Guangying, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of
China's National People's Congress (NPC), and former Japanese
prime minister and JCRC Honorary Chairman Noboru Takeshita
attended the signing ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The JCRC, founded on July 1, 1997, has more than 60 members,
including several Japanese railway companies, rolling stock plants
and commercial councils.
</P>
<P>
The JCRC has trained a number of professionals working with
China's Railway Ministry since November 1997. 
