<HEADLINE> Chinese State Councillor Meets HK Business Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Chinese State Councillor Wu Yi
said here today that the economic cooperation and trade between
Hong Kong and the inland area of China should be enhanced.
</P>
<P>
During her meeting with a delegation of the Hong Kong Trade
Development Council (HKTDC), headed by its chairman Fung Vicpor,
Wu said that the two-way trade between the two sides has enjoyed
rapid development since China began to adopt reform and open-up
policy 20 years ago.
</P>
<P>
The trade volume of the two sides reached 50.7 billion US
dollars last year, and Hong Kong was the second largest trade
partner of the inland area of China.
</P>
<P>
Wu said that the two sides should bring into full play their
advantages to strengthen the cooperation in the
hi-tech sector because such cooperation has an important bearing
on maintaining Hong Kong's status of an international center of
economy, trade, finance and information.
</P>
<P>
She extended welcome to the first HKTDC delegation to Beijing
since Hong Kong returned to its motherland last July.
</P>
<P>
She also spoke highly of HKTDC's important role in promoting
trade between Hong Kong and other parts of the world.
</P>
<P>
Wu expressed her hope that the HKTDC would make new
contributions to the advancement of economic cooperation and trade
between inland areas of China and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Fung said that Hong Kong business community attaches greater
importance to the economic cooperation with the mainland, and
hopes to make contributions to reform of mainland's state-owned
enterprises, development of the central and western region and
the advanced technology field.
</P>
<P>
The delegation is here at the invitation of the China Council
for Promotion of Trade.  
</P>
</TEXT>
