<HEADLINE> China Utilizes 10 percent More Overseas Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 16 (Xinhua) -- China brought in 8.59 billion
U.S. dollars in overseas funds in the first quarter of this year,
up 9.68 percent over the same period last year, according to the
Chinese Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The government approved 3,971 overseas-financed projects during
that period, with the contractual value amounting to 8.72 billion
U.S. dollars, a ten percent increase.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, overseas funds introduced by Sino-foreign joint
ventures dropped 4.06 percent to 3.4 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Sino-foreign cooperative businesses and solely foreign-funded
firms brought in 1.98 and 3.12 billion U.S. dollars in overseas
funds, respectively, up by 35 and 12.53 percent.
</P>
<P>
All the three types of businesses posted increases in the
amount of their newly approved contracts involving overseas funds,
reaching 3.16, 1.88 and 3.61 billion U.S. dollars, respectively,
up 10.85, 0.75 and 13.69 percent. 
</P>
