<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Miner Dies in Rescue Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, April 16 (Xinhua) -- A miner died in north
Tanzania's Arusha Wednesday as he tried to rescue others who were
buried by a landslide, Daily News reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The miner, 25, died of fumes as teams struggled to rescue an
estimated 100 trapped miners with heavy-duty pumps.
</P>
<P>
The miners were trapped following a downpour which caused the
landslide at the Mererani tanzanite mine last Thursday evening.
</P>
<P>
The Zanzibar President, Salmin Amour, has conveyed a message
of condolences to the Arusha Regional Commissioner following the
Mererani tragedy.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a three-member parliamentary team has left for
Arusha to assess the situation of the disaster. The team is
expected to present a report to the parliament on the casualties
and future preventive measures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
