<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mobil Establishes Environmental Education Fund in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 16 (Xinhua) -- The Mobil Oil Company today
donated 10 million yuan (1.2 million U.S. dollars) to China's
State Environmental Protection Administration (SEPA) to set up a
fund to support the country's environmental education plans.
</P>
<P>
The Mobil China Environmental Education Fund will be used to
aid a series of programs on environmental protection publicity and
education in a five-year period starting in 1998, especially
China's key programs in the field.
</P>
<P>
The first project supported by the fund is the Mayors' Seminar
on the Protection of Taihu, Chaohu and Dianchi lakes, which has
already started.
</P>
<P>
SEPA's Deputy-Director Zhu Guangyao said at today's inaugural
ceremony that environmental protection work is facing growing
challenges as a result of increasing global deterioration and
limited funds.
</P>
<P>
"It is imperative that we bring environmental protection onto
the agenda," he said.
</P>
<P>
Zhu called on more domestic and international companies to
participate in environmental protection activities in China.
</P>
<P>
Lucille Cavanaugh, chairwoman of Mobil Asia Pacific Private
Co. Ltd., said that the fund is Mobil's inaugural step in ensuring
that China will be renowned as an environmentally sound and secure
country, adding that Mobil will "spare no efforts in supporting
China's modernization and environmental protection requirements
now and in the future."
</P>
<P>
Mobil, a global energy company, has more than 20 offices in
China, including Beijing, Shanghai, Guangzhou and Wuhan. Its
business in China can be traced back to 1894 when it set up its
first representative office in Shanghai.  
</P>
