<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-16 08:55 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran's to Promote Non-oil Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 16 (Xinhua) -- The Iranian government has decided
to promote non-oil exports in order to reduce the impacts of the
reduction of oil revenue on the country's economy, the Iranian
official news agency IRNA reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The cabinet ministers discussed ways to encourage non-oil
exports on Wednesday afternoon and decided to seriously follow
specific policies to minimize the damage of the sharp fall in oil
incomes on the economy.
</P>
<P>
They discussed a report by the Plan and Budget Organization
(PBO) on the impact of shrinking oil revenues on the country's
economy, but stressing that although a drop in oil prices will
reduce the government's revenues in the new Iranian year (started
on March 21), it is a "blessing in disguise" for the government
since it will be compelled to move toward an oil-free economy.
</P>
<P>
The government will formulate and implement plans to promote
non-oil exports and remove obstacles hindering exports, improve
quality and quantity of products, increase output and
competitiveness of Iranian products at international markets, the
IRNA said.
</P>
<P>
Despite desperate efforts to promote the status of non-oil
exports, Iran's customs announced recently that the exports had
fallen by 3.1 percent to 3 billion U.S. dollars during the past
Iranian year, much less than the figure of 5.5 billion dollars
projected in the second five year development plan (1995-2000).
</P>
<P>
Officials and experts said that the instability of policies
and complicated procedures were the main hurdles for the country
to promote non-oil exports.
</P>
<P>
In order to save its limited foreign capitals, the government
raised the rate of foreign exchanges sold to Iranian travelers
from 3,000 rials to 4,800 rials against the dollar in order to
prevent any unnecessary trips.
</P>
<P>
The IRNA said that the cabinet also decided to take measures
to eliminate hindrances and restrictions on way of investment, to
protect the vulnerable masses through subsidies, control and
reduce current government expenditures and give priority to
implementation of development projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
