<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Released Mayor Announces No Changes in Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 16 (Xinhua) -- The released Tehran Mayor
Gholamhussein Karbaschi has announced that he has not changed his
opinion on the city's administration after an 11-day imprisonment,
the Iranian official news agency IRNA reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"I am of the same opinion that I have held during my services
as the mayor of Tehran and you can see that my outlooks have not
changed," Karbaschi was quoted by IRNA as saying on Wednesday
after he was released on bail from the prison upon an order from
the supreme leader Ayatollah Ali Khamenei.
</P>
<P>
The mayor was detained on April 4 by the hard-line judiciary on
charges of embezzlement, misuse of public fund and mismanagement,
triggering a new round of factional fighting between the
hardliners and the moderates.
</P>
<P>
Karbaschi once again rejected the charges against him, saying
that no form of embezzlement or misuse of public funds have taken
place. However, he noted that there is a possibility of a flaw
when one takes responsibility and makes decisions on the planning
for the city.
</P>
<P>
He said he believed that there might be better ways to settle
the issues, expressing the hope that these problems would be
thoroughly scrutinized with the show of patience and perseverance.
</P>
<P>
Referring to his release, Karbaschi said that he was informed
ten minutes before his release that he was going to be set free
from the jail.
</P>
<P>
He thanked the people who showed warm welcome to him in front
of his house and shouted slogans in support of him.
</P>
<P>
According to a statement issued by the district court of
Tehran, IRNA said, Karbaschi was released on bail at the request
of President Mohammad Khatami, who enjoyed strong support from the
Tehran mayor during the presidential elections in last May.
</P>
<P>
After agreeing with the president's request, Khamenei issued a
decree to the judiciary head Ayatollah Mohammad Yazdi asking him
to free the detained mayor "on basis of surety for the bail."
</P>
<P>
Khamenei also instructed the judicial body to pursue the case
"in an atmosphere free from any tension and according to the laws
governing the nation."
</P>
<P>
Local newspapers said that Former President Hashemi Rafsanjani
had launched "extensive efforts" to free Karbaschi after his
detention and convinced Khamenei to agree with the mayors release
in order to prevent further tension between the two rival
factions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
