<HEADLINE> British Prime Minister to Visit Saudi Arabia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, April 16 (Xinhua) -- British Prime Minister Tony
Blair will visit Saudi Arabia Saturday as part of his Mideast
tour aimed at trying to find means of reinvigorating the
stalled Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Saudi Arabia, Blair will hold talks with
Saudi King Fahd Ibn Abdul-Aziz and other government officials on
how to push the Mideast peace process forward, Diplomatic sources
in Saudi Arabia was quoted by Kuwait News Agency as saying.
</P>
<P>
The European states, in particular France and Britain which
currently chairs the European Union, are deeply worried about the
freezing of the Middle East peace process and have called on
Israel time and again to abide by the agreements it signed with
the Palestinians, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
But they said that Blair would not present to Saudi Arabia or
other parties a package of British or European ideas aimed at
ending the stalemate in the peace process during his trip.
</P>
<P>
However, while not spelling out any peace initiatives, Blair
would "attempt to find a better atmosphere for resuming the talks
between the Palestinians and Israel."
</P>
<P>
The Mideast peace process has been stalled for over a year due
to Israeli intransigent policies.
</P>
<P>
Blair's Mideast trip will also include Egypt, Israel and the
Palestinian self-rule areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
