<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT April 16 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH -- Chea Mun, commander of the Cambodian Army's
Fourth Military Zone, told Xinhua Thursday that he cannot confirm
reports that former Khmer Rouge leader Pol Pot is dead.
</P>
<P>
"As far as I have learned, Da Mok, current head of the Khmer
Rouge, took Pol Pot to Thailand a few days ago when they were
retreating from their Anlong Veng stronghold," said the Cambodian
commander, who is in charge of the military operations against
Anlong Veng. "As the situation along the Cambodian-Thai border is
still complicated, it is very difficult to get accurate
information about Pol Pot and Da Mok for the time being," Chea Mun
said.
</P>
<P>
Pol Pot, 71, has reportedly died of heart attack on Wednesday
night. (Cambodia-Pol Pot, Updates)
</P>
