<HEADLINE> Senior Officials Going to State Enterprises to Act as Supervisors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 16 (Xinhua) -- China has launched a program of
sending high-ranking government officials to 500 state-run major
enterprises to help as supervisors, according to today's Wenhui
Daily.
</P>
<P>
The ministerial-level officials will mainly oversee the use and
value of enterprises' property and the actions of cadres, as a
basis for future use of the cadres. The program has at least 510
applicants up to late March.
</P>
<P>
The paper reports that 100 groups of 5 government officials
each will be sent to the 500 state enterprises, with one group in
charge of five enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Each group will have a minister or vice-minister, a director or
deputy director, and three office workers. The first lot will have
150 officials.
</P>
<P>
Song Defu, the personnel minister, says that these officials
will not get involved in the internal affairs of enterprises,
except to check accounts, and that ministers of certain industries
can not check enterprises in related industries and these
officials can not serve consecutive terms. 
</P>
