<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 16 (Xinhua) -- The Association of Southeast
Asian Nations (ASEAN) should stand united to move forward towards
the integration of regional economies, ASEAN Secretary-General
Rodolfo Severino said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN should develop a collective voice in dealing with the
financial crisis affecting the region as it has both global and
regional dimensions, he told reporters after meeting Malaysian
Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad here in his capacity as the
grouping's new secretary-general.
</P>
<P>
A collective voice was necessary as it would greatly contribute
towards influencing the evolution of an international financial
system, he said, adding "Currency trading should be an important
element of this evolution."
</P>
