<HEADLINE> Romania: New Government Validated by the Parliament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Romania's Parliament validated
the new cabinet, which is headed by Prime Minister Radu Vasile,
with a majority of 317 to 124 votes Wednesday evening.
</P>
<P>
The parliament also approved a program presented by the prime
minister.
</P>
<P>
The task of the new cabinet is to "get us out quickly from the
deadlock we have floundered in. If we are not able to, we
will leave by ourselves, inviting someone better to replace us,"
Vasile said when addressing the parliament before the validation.
</P>
<P>
Vasile said the guiding principles for his cabinet would be:
social reform for the recognition and affirmation of moral values;
property rights; a decent living standard; accelerated
institutional reform; and the restructuring and upgrading of
industry to insure economic growth.
</P>
<P>
The cabinet will also work to develop agriculture, and
to distribute costs fairly, he added.
</P>
<P>
Integration with European and Euro-Atlantic political, economic
and security organizations is the key issue of foreign policy,
Vasile said, adding that good relations with neighboring
countries and a strategic partnership with the U.S is also a major
goal of foreign policy.
</P>
<P>
Romania will also continue to develop ties with Russia, Vasile
said.
</P>
<P>
On April 2, President Emil Constantinescu officially authorized
Radu Vasile, general secretary of the largest National Peasant's
Party in the coalition, to form a new cabinet.
</P>
<P>
The former government, which was headed by Victor Ciorbea,
resigned on March 30 after failing to solve a government crisis.
</P>
</TEXT>
