<HEADLINE> Croatia and Macedonia of Same View on SEU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Croatia and Macedonia share a
similar view on the establishment of the Southern European Union,
Assembly (parliament) of Croatia President Vlatko Pavletic said.
</P>
<P>
Pavletic made the remark in a news conference after meeting
with Macedonian Assembly (parliament) President Tito Petkovski,
who arrived here Wednesday with a delegation for a three-day visit.
</P>
<P>
The two parliamentary chiefs held talks on strengthening
bilateral cooperation and discussed regional issues.
</P>
<P>
Macedonia supports all multi-lateral economic cooperation that
is profitable, but is opposed to the establishment of political
alliances or confederations of any form, Pavletic said.
</P>
<P>
Both Croatia and Macedonia hope to be admitted into the
European Union and the North Atlantic Treaty Organization, and
both are willing to develop market economies, he said.
</P>
<P>
The expected visit by Croatian President Franjo Tudjman to
Macedonia this year affirms the good ties that exist between the
two countries, Petkovski said, adding that the two countries will
sign a series of cooperative agreements.
</P>
<P>
Petkovski thanked Croatia for its understanding attitude on the
Kosovo crisis and warned of the possible spread of the conflict to
Macedonian soil. 
</P>
</TEXT>
