<HEADLINE> Hungarian-Russian Trade Increases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Trade between Hungary and Russia
was on the rise and it increased by 300 million U.S. Dollars in
1997.
</P>
<P>
Trade between the two countries reached 3.1 billion dollars last
year, registering a sharp rise from the 2.8 billion dollars in the
previous year, the Russian business office to Budapest announced
wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Hungary exported 900 million dollars' worth of products to
Russia and its imports were worth 2.2 billion dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
Three categories of products constituted 80 percent of
Hungary's exports to Russia: foods (40 percent), medicine (20
percent) and buses (20 percent).
</P>
<P>
Hungary imported from Russia energy and industrial raw
materials. 
