<HEADLINE> Andean Community Participates in ALCA Process </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, April 15 (Xinhua) -- The Andean Community, the second
largest economic bloc in the South American region, declared
Wednesday its participation in preliminary negotiations for the
creation of the Free Trade Zone of the Americas (ALCA).
</P>
<P>
In past months the Andean Community had participated in some
meetings organized to assure that concerns of each country were
included in the ALCA negotiations, Ana Maria de Reategui, general
secretary of the bloc, said in an interview with Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
In the ministerial meeting of the American continent held in
March in Costa Rica, the Andean Community stressed that
differences in the development levels of countries concerned must
be considered as the principle for the ALCA negotiations.
</P>
<P>
Ana Maria de Reategui said the active role of the Andean
Community is also shown by its wish to obtain the presidency of
three of the nine negotiationing groups for the creation of ALCA.
</P>
<P>
The Andean Community is participating in the negotiations as a
bloc, she said.
</P>
<P>
Members of the Andean Community are Venezuela, Colombia,
Ecuador, Peru and Bolivia, while the Common Market of the South
(Mercosur), the main South-American economic bloc, is consists of
Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay and Uruguay. 
</P>
