<HEADLINE> Czech President in Stable Condition After Surgery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Czech President Vaclav Havel's
physical condition is reported as excellent following an
emergency operation in Austria for a perforated intestine, said a
medical bulletin Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Doctors at the Innsbruck University Hospital, where Havel was
in surgery for nearly four hours on Tuesday, said the president
was recovering satisfactorily in a ward and his condition was
being closely monitored.
</P>
<P>
Innsbruck's chief surgeon said he removed about 30 centimeters
of the president's large intestine.
</P>
<P>
Although Havel's condition is described as excellent, doctors
still cautioned that "serious complications are possible within
days."
</P>
<P>
The head of the hospital's intensive care unit said ``he is in
very good condition."
</P>
<P>
Havel also spoke by telephone to Austrian President Thomas
Klestil as well as Czech politicians.
</P>
<P>
Havel's conditioned developed during the Easter weekend while
he was spending a vacation with his wife in the Austrian resort of
Tirol.
</P>
<P>
Havel, a former playwright, who led Prague's overthrow of
communism in 1989, narrowly won re-election for a final five-year
term in January.
</P>
<P>
He has vowed to get closer to the people, admitting that his
position has made him too remote. 
</P>
