<DOCNO> XIE19980416.0296 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Product Quality Stable </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Latest quarterly official product
quality inspection report show China's large and medium-sized
enterprises continue to perform well.
</P>
<P>
The quality rating of their products was more than 21
percentage points higher than smaller factories, according to the
China State Bureau of Quality and Technical Supervision.
</P>
<P>
Large enterprises have shown steady improvement in product
quality control in recent years. They were given a quality rating
of 93.3 percent, 4.6 percentage points above the previous
quarterly sample product quality inspection.
</P>
<P>
Medium-sized enterprises achieved an average rating of 91.9
percent, their best figure since 1995.
</P>
<P>
However, products made by small factories only registered a
70.2 percent rating, 6.3 percentage points below the national
average.
</P>
<P>
The national average product quality rate was only 76.5
percent, said the bureau.
</P>
<P>
The quality inspection for the first quarter covered 1,252
products from 1,050 enterprises, 71.4 percent of which were small
factories.
</P>
<P>
The bureau's report indicated quality problems with some
medical equipment, food and mining equipment were still serious.
</P>
<P>
It also noted that small factories, especially
collectively-owned and private works, are the main factors
preventing any further advance in product quality.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
