<HEADLINE> Floods Sweep Away 40 Houses in S. Sumatra, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Flash floods swept about 40
houses and killed one person in Karang Dapo Lama village,
Indonesia's South Sumatra province before dawn on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
At least three people have gone missing in the floods that
occurred after the Betung river, a tributary of Musi river,
overflowed, Antara News Agency reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The floods also destroyed 40 hectares of farmland and carried
away thousands of cows and goats.
</P>
<P>
Local residents said they were sleeping when the flash floods
hit the village.
</P>
<P>
The local government has sent a rescue team to the village,
spokesman for the provincial administration H. Agustiar Effendi
was quoted as saying. 
</P>
</TEXT>
