<HEADLINE> Blatter in Croatia for FIFA Presidency Support </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, April 15 (Xinhua) -- FIFA secretary-general Joseph
Blatter, one of the two candidates for FIFA presidency, was in
Croatia on Wednesday to drum up support for his candidature.
</P>
<P>
"The purpose of my visit is the possibility of getting a
positive response to my candidature for the next FIFA presidency,"
he told a press conference.
</P>
<P>
The current FIFA president, Brazilian Joao Havelange, is due to
step down on June 8, two days before the World Cup kicks off in
France.
</P>
<P>
Almost all of the members of the European Football Union (UEFA)
have said they will back Blatter's rival -- UEFA president Lannart
Johansson of Sweden -- as Havelange's replacement.
</P>
<P>
Blatter, however, seemed to have met with some success in his
trip to Zagreb on Wednesday, during which he met Croatian
President Franjo Tudjman and watched FC Croatia beat Zagreb 3-0.
</P>
<P>
Croatian Football Federation chief Branko Miksa ended the press
conference by saying that he had been delighted that "the next
FIFA president" had come to Zagreb.
</P>
<P>
Blatter, for his part, said that he would not be surprised if
the Croatian national team reached the quarter-finals of the World
Cup. 
</P>
</TEXT>
