<HEADLINE> Juventus Loses but Reach Cup Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Juventus reached the European
Champions' League final on aggregate victory despite their 3-2
loss to Monaco in the semifinals on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Italian champions, with a 4-1 cushion from the first leg in
Turin, stretched their lead in the 14th minute through substitute
Nicola Amoruso.
</P>
<P>
Monaco levelled the scoreline seven minutes from the break as
defender Philippe Leonard equalised with a tremendous 30-meter
free-kick.
</P>
<P>
In the second half, Thierry Henry put Monaco 2-1 up in the 50th
minute, but Juventus' in-form striker Del Piero volleyed a
magnificent goal in the 74th minute to equalise at 2-2.
</P>
<P>
Monace finally won the match on substitute Robert Spehar's goal
seven minutes from time, but that was not enough to send the home
side to the final. 
</P>
