<HEADLINE> U.S. Dollar Slips Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 15 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. dollar continued to
slip against major foreign currencies Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The dollar also was down against the German mark but was little
changed against other major currencies.
</P>
<P>
In late New York trading, the dollar was quoted at 1.7979
marks, down from 1.8020 late Tuesday. The U.S. currency also
changed hands at 129.36 yen, down from 129.55 yen.
</P>
<P>
Traders were worried the Bank of Japan, the nation's central
bank, would intervene in currency markets, as it did last week, to
prop up the yen.
</P>
<P>
The dollar's slip against the mark came as investor sentiment
shifted slightly on the perception that German interest rates were
rising and that U.S. economic fundamentals weren't as strong given
Tuesday's weak retail sales report.
</P>
<P>
Other late dollar rates in New York, compared with late
Tuesday: 1.4928 Swiss francs, up from 1.4927; 6.0385 French
francs, unchanged; 1,782.00 Italian lire, down from 1,782.85; and
1.4395 Canadian dollars, up from 1.4335.
</P>
<P>
The British pound was quoted at 1.6852 dollars, unchanged from
Tuesday. 
</P>
